This paper deals with the formalization and transformation of graph-shaped data, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graph traversal and query languages also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the compatibility and interoperability of different systems, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE).
